				<p class='posted_info desc lighter ipsType_small'>
					Posted <abbr class="published" itemprop="commentTime" title="2012-12-02T05:57:27+00:00">02 December 2012 - 12:57 AM</abbr>
					
				</p>
				
				<div itemprop="commentText" class='post entry-content '>
					PHP requires you to be explicit.  That&#39;s not necessarily a bad thing.  For example, if you can import wildcard namespaces:<br /><br /><pre class='prettyprint lang-auto linenums:0'>
namespace A{
class Foo{
    public function bar(){
        echo &quot;A&quot;;
    }
}
}

namespace B{
class Foo{
    public function bar(){
        echo &quot;B&quot;;
    }
}
}

namespace C{
use \A;
use \B;
&#036;a = new Foo();
&#036;a-&gt;bar();
}
</pre><br />What&#39;s echoed?
					
					<br />
					<p class='edit'>
							<strong>Edited by xylex, 02 December 2012 - 12:59 AM.</strong>
							
						</p>
				</div>
				
				
