					<blockquote class='ipsBlockquote' data-author="&#39;Jessica&#39;" data-cid="1401432" data-time="1356572327" data-date="26 December 2012 - 08:38 PM"><p>&quot; mind elaborating why &#39;goto&#39; is added in PHP 5.3 when its been argued as a misfeature by many experienced coders? You&#39;ve gotta give people choices, let them make their own decision on how to write their scripts.&quot;<br /><br />Good job answering your own question&#33;<br /></p></blockquote><br />umm whats your point? PHP right now does not give us a choice for wildcard import, thats what I&#39;ve been arguing about.<br /><br /><br /><blockquote class='ipsBlockquote' data-author="&#39;requinix&#39;" data-cid="1401440" data-time="1356577564" data-date="26 December 2012 - 10:06 PM"><p>By the way, here&#39;s a question. Given the pseudo-code<br /><pre class='prettyprint lang-php linenums:0'>use Fruit\*;
